args:
When the party discovers a strange place with a
high concentration of black mana, it threatens
to end their journey. But then Ilia suggests that
a body crafted from the Other would be immune
to the substance, causing the prince to move on
and find Sheila's soul lamenting her sins.
This fell miasma is frightfully thick;\nwe cannot even see what lies ahead.
Merely standing near it makes me feel ill.
High concentrations of black mana found.\nIt would be dangerous for organic life\nto pass through, so I will proceed alone.
Actually, Laxi, it's not any safer for you.
That black mana could do all sorts of\nscrewy things to your core.
And not even the greatest of alchemists\ncould put you back to normal if that\nhappened, so you'd better hang back.
Well, there's definitely something back\nthere, but I'm out of ideas as to how\nwe'll actually reach it.
Oh, that's easy. We send you.
Uh, but what about the whole ＂dangerous\nfor organic life＂ bit?
Well, here's the deal: this miasma is\nmainly comprised of black mana, yeah?
Now, if it was made of some other kind\nof toxin, it'd be as dangerous to you as\nthe rest of us.
But you're resistant to black mana—\nhell, your body is pretty much an\naggregation of the stuff.

Yep! See, 'cause your body was created
from a piece of the Other, and HIS body
was an aggregate of black mana itself.
...Back me up here, Zethia.
I believe that to be accurate, yes.
When the Other was born, black mana\ncame rushing into this world.
The Other took anger and hate and all the\nother negative emotions and used them to\ngive form to his body.
All of which to say, black mana shouldn't\ndo boo to you, {player_name}.
You can pass through this miasma cloud\nand walk away whistling!
Well, I suppose you'd know, seeing as you\nwere there when the Other was born...
Okay. If there's something in there,\nI'll be sure to find it.
Wait. You...want to come with me?
Sheila's taking action on her own...!
Perhaps she's feeling something upon\nreturning to her homeland after so long.
Will you take her with you.\n{player_name}?
Hey, that's right! Sheila was also made\nfrom a piece of the Other!
Yes, and she lost her heart as a result of\nthe corruption within that creature.
Even with her heart lost to her as it is now,\nshe could at least run back and let us know\nif some ill fate befell you in that mist.
I think we would all rest a bit easier\nknowing you were not taking this task\non alone. So then, what say you?
Sure, Sheila. Let's do this together.
Though your body may be of the Other,\nthe spirit that lies within is yours alone.\nYour safety is by no means assured.
Keep it strong, that it is not profaned\nby the black mana.
I promise we'll both come back safe.\nJust hang tight until then.
I shall pray for your safe return.
(I'm tired from all the fighting, but I don't\nsense any effect from the black mana.\nGuess that means Ilia was right.)
Wait a second. That seems to be your\nvoice, but I don't see your lips moving.
Maybe it's an auditory hallucination\nof some kind?
Anyway, it's coming from up this way,\nso let's go check it out.
That was definitely your voice, Sheila.\nCould that be your heart?!
